Papers are starting to emerge... the first since I joined has been submitted for publication.</gtr:impact><gtr:partnerContribution>Although the collaboration is based at PSI, it encompasses many partners from around Europe. PSI is providing the source, much of the equipment, substantial manpower. (My estimate of 5 M CHF is probably wildly inaccurate.) The collaboration has existed for quite some years but we only joined it in 2014.</gtr:partnerContribution><gtr:piContribution>We are taking on responsibility for coordination of key parts of the neutron EDM project, in particular helium magnetometry, Ramsey cell design, and systematics analysis. (We also built, many years ago, the original apparatus on which the current project is based...)</gtr:piContribution><gtr:sector>Public</gtr:sector><gtr:start>2014-01-01</gtr:start></gtr:collaborationOutput></gtr:collaborationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:impactSummaryOutput><gtr:description>This work is regularly used for outreach purposes, to inspire the next generation of (potential) physicists.</gtr:description><gtr:firstYearOfImpact>2014</gtr:firstYearOfImpact><gtr:id>5E033BF2-5720-46AE-A7FC-57C9B94162AF</gtr:id><gtr:impactTypes><gtr:impactType>Cultural</gtr:impactType></gtr:impactTypes><gtr:sector>Education</gtr:sector></gtr:impactSummaryOutput></gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:description>This grant funds development work towards one of the most precise and exquisite measurements that it's possible to make in physics: the search for the so-called Electric Dipole Moment (EDM) of the neutron. This is a tiny distortion of the structure of the neutron (a subatomic particle), perhaps a billion times smaller than anything that LHC is capable of detecting. It is critically important for helping us to understand the origin of all of the matter in the Universe - including all of us, and the stars and planets - since the size of this subatomic distortion is intimately related to the question of the difference between matter and antimatter, which led to our Universe being matter-dominated. We use a sort of atomic clock to study the behaviour of neutrons in strong electric fields, which allow us ever increasing sensitivity in the measurement.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>Findings will be of immense importance to theorists trying to understand the origins of matter in the Universe.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>A7DFB69E-F054-4DC2-A093-B7CB47590091</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Education</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors><gtr:url>https://www.psi.ch/nedm/publications</gtr:url></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/2183252C-4C70-4DCF-B97A-1A1C65826242"><gtr:id>2183252C-4C70-4DCF-B97A-1A1C65826242</gtr:id><gtr:title>Gravitational depolarization of ultracold neutrons: Comparison with data</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Physical Review D</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/b7ac1c3177a40c6eda59f1168459a73c"><gtr:id>b7ac1c3177a40c6eda59f1168459a73c</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Afach S</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2015-01-01</gtr:date></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/9C283859-1B3F-4D84-8255-4BFF7CE46C50"><gtr:id>9C283859-1B3F-4D84-8255-4BFF7CE46C50</gtr:id><gtr:title>Revised experimental upper limit on the electric dipole moment of the neutron</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Physical Review D</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/fbb39754ad9736e9a1b75aa9549b99d2"><gtr:id>fbb39754ad9736e9a1b